Directions.1: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

Directions.2: Place frozen French fries in a large bowl. Add olive oil and toss to coat. Season with salt and toss to coat again.

Directions.3: Spread out French fries in the basket of the air fryer, making sure to not overcrowd, and cook for 10 minutes. Turn fries over using a spatula and continue cooking until desired crispness, 2 to 4 minutes more.
